---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = "BC PNP Calculator FAQ & Troubleshooting Guide";
const description = "Answers to the most common BC PNP calculator questions. Troubleshoot errors, understand terminology, and get unstuck.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 sm:py-20">
    
    <!-- Hero Header -->
    <header class="mb-16 text-center">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-20 h-20 bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-500 to-orange-600 rounded-3xl mb-8 shadow-xl shadow-amber-200">
        <svg class="w-10 h-10 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8.228 9c.549-1.165 2.03-2 3.772-2 2.21 0 4 1.343 4 3 0 1.4-1.278 2.575-3.006 2.907-.542.104-.994.54-.994 1.093m0 3h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-black text-slate-900 tracking-tight leading-tight mb-6">
        <span class="text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-600 to-orange-600">FAQ</span> & Troubleshooting
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        Got stuck? Here are answers to the most common BC PNP calculator questions and problems.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <div class="space-y-16">
      
      <!-- Troubleshooting Section -->
      <section>
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-b from-red-50 to-white rounded-[2rem] p-8 sm:p-10 border border-red-100">
          <div class="text-center mb-10">
             <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black text-slate-900 mb-3">Troubleshooting Common Errors</h2>
             <p class="text-slate-600">Why is your score lower than expected?</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-[1.5rem] shadow-sm border-l-4 border-red-500">
              <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 text-lg mb-2">"My score dropped by 10 points."</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed text-sm">
                <strong>Check this:</strong> Did you cross a wage threshold? Wages like $24.99 and $25.00 are in different brackets. Also check your "District" selection. Area 1 (Vancouver) gives 0 points, but Area 2 (Squamish, Abbotsford) gives 5.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-[1.5rem] shadow-sm border-l-4 border-red-500">
              <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 text-lg mb-2">"I can't find my University on the list."</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed text-sm">
                <strong>Fix:</strong> BC PNP doesn't have a dropdown of universities. You simply select "Bachelor's Degree" or "Master's Degree". Only <em>where</em> you got it matters (BC vs. Canada vs. Foreign).
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-[1.5rem] shadow-sm border-l-4 border-red-500">
              <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 text-lg mb-2">"The wage slider is stuck."</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed text-sm">
                <strong>Fix:</strong> Ensure you are entering the <em>hourly</em> rate. If you only know your annual salary, divide it by 52 weeks and then by your standard weekly hours (usually 40).
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Detailed FAQ Section -->
      <section>
        <div class="text-center mb-10">
          <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black text-slate-900 mb-3">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        </div>
        
        <div class="space-y-4">
           <!-- Category: Eligibility -->
           <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-widest text-sm pl-4 mt-8 mb-4">Eligibility & Rules</h3>
           
          <details class="group bg-white rounded-[1.5rem] border border-slate-200 overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
            <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
              <span class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-lg pr-4">Do I strictly need a job offer to apply?</span>
              <span class="w-8 h-8 bg-amber-100 rounded-full flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center text-amber-600 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
                </svg>
              </span>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
              <p>For almost all BC PNP streams (Skills Immigration, Tech, Health Authority), <strong>YES</strong>. You need an indeterminate, full-time job offer. The only major exceptions are some "International Post-Graduate" streams for science/health graduates from BC institutions.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
          
          <details class="group bg-white rounded-[1.5rem] border border-slate-200 overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
            <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
              <span class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-lg pr-4">Can self-employed people apply?</span>
              <span class="w-8 h-8 bg-amber-100 rounded-full flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center text-amber-600 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
                </svg>
              </span>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
              <p>Generally, <strong>NO</strong>. The Skills Immigration stream is for employees. If you own more than 10% of the company offering you the job, you are ineligible. You would need to look at the "Entrepreneur Immigration" stream instead.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
          
          <details class="group bg-white rounded-[1.5rem] border border-slate-200 overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
            <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
              <span class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-lg pr-4">What counts as "Directly Related Work Experience"?</span>
              <span class="w-8 h-8 bg-amber-100 rounded-full flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center text-amber-600 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
                </svg>
              </span>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
              <p>This is strict. If your BC job offer is for a "Software Engineer" (NOC 21231), experience as a "Web Designer" might count if the duties overlap significantly, but experience as a "Sales Manager" will absolutely not count towards related exp points, even if it was at a tech company.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

           <!-- Category: After Application -->
           <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-widest text-sm pl-4 mt-8 mb-4">After You Apply</h3>

          <details class="group bg-white rounded-[1.5rem] border border-slate-200 overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
            <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
              <span class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-lg pr-4">Can I update my profile after submitting?</span>
              <span class="w-8 h-8 bg-amber-100 rounded-full flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center text-amber-600 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
                </svg>
              </span>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
              <p>Yes. Your profile stays in the pool for up to 12 months (or until invited). If you get a raise, complete a new degree, or improve your English scores, you can—and should—update your profile to increase your score.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
          
           <details class="group bg-white rounded-[1.5rem] border border-slate-200 overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
            <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
              <span class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-lg pr-4">Why are applications refused?</span>
              <span class="w-8 h-8 bg-amber-100 rounded-full flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center text-amber-600 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
                </svg>
              </span>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
              <p>The #1 reason is <strong>Inflation of Information</strong>. If you claimed you earn $30/hr but your paystubs show $28/hr, you will be refused. If you claimed 3 years of experience but only prove 2.5 years, you will be refused. The officer must verify that your score at the time of application matched or exceeded the draw cut-off.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Glossary -->
      <section>
        <div class="text-center mb-10">
          <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black text-slate-900 mb-3">BC PNP Glossary</h2>
        </div>
        
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-[1.5rem]">
            <p class="font-black text-slate-900 mb-1">SIRS</p>
            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Skills Immigration Registration System. The "pool" where your points are calculated.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-[1.5rem]">
            <p class="font-black text-slate-900 mb-1">ITA</p>
            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Invitation to Apply. The "golden ticket" you get if your score is high enough.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-[1.5rem]">
            <p class="font-black text-slate-900 mb-1">NOC</p>
            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">National Occupational Classification. The code that defines your job duties.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-[1.5rem]">
            <p class="font-black text-slate-900 mb-1">TEER</p>
            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Training, Education, Experience, Responsibility. The category (0-5) of your NOC code.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-[1.5rem]">
            <p class="font-black text-slate-900 mb-1">IPG</p>
            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">International Post-Graduate. A special stream for Masters/PhD grads in sciences.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-[1.5rem]">
            <p class="font-black text-slate-900 mb-1">CLB</p>
            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Canadian Language Benchmark. The standard scale for English/French proficiency.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <section>
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-red-600 to-red-700 rounded-[2rem] p-10 sm:p-12 text-center text-white">
          <h3 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black mb-4">Still Have Questions?</h3>
          <p class="text-red-100 mb-8 max-w-md mx-auto">Run your specific scenario through the calculator to get a definite answer.</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center bg-white text-red-600 px-8 py-4 rounded-[1.5rem] font-black text-lg hover:bg-red-50 transition-colors shadow-xl">
            Start Calculation
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"></path>
            </svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Related Guides -->
      <section class="pt-8 border-t border-slate-200">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-black text-slate-900 uppercase tracking-widest mb-8 text-center">Related Guides</h2>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <a href="/articles/how-to-use-bc-pnp-calculator-2026" class="group bg-white p-6 rounded-[1.5rem] border border-slate-100 hover:border-red-200 hover:shadow-lg transition-all">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 group-hover:text-red-600 mb-1">How to Use the Calculator</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm">Step-by-step instructions for 2026.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/articles/bc-pnp-vs-crs-calculator" class="group bg-white p-6 rounded-[1.5rem] border border-slate-100 hover:border-red-200 hover:shadow-lg transition-all">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 group-hover:text-red-600 mb-1">BC PNP vs CRS</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm">Which system is right for you?</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/articles/maximize-bc-pnp-score-tips" class="group bg-white p-6 rounded-[1.5rem] border border-slate-100 hover:border-red-200 hover:shadow-lg transition-all">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 group-hover:text-red-600 mb-1">Maximize Your Score</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm">Hidden points and Reddit strategies.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/articles/bc-pnp-calculator-for-tech" class="group bg-white p-6 rounded-[1.5rem] border border-slate-100 hover:border-red-200 hover:shadow-lg transition-all">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 group-hover:text-red-600 mb-1">Tech & High-Demand</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm">Special lookup for priority jobs.</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
